#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choosing this context menu option has exactly the same effect as clicking "
"the <guibutton>&nbsp;&plus;&nbsp;New Contact&nbsp;</guibutton> button on the "
"Toolbar. See <link linkend=\"how-to-add-a-new-contact\">chapter 2 above</"
"link> for complete details."
msgstr ""
"Izbira te možnosti kontekstnega menija ima popolnoma enak učinek kot klik na "
"gumb <guibutton>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nov stik&nbsp;</guibutton> v orodni "
"vrstici. Za vse podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"how-to-add-a-new-contact"
"\">poglavje 2 zgoraj</link>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>G</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"user-"
"group-new.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject>New "
"Group</guimenu>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>G</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"user-"
"group-new.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject>Nova "
"skupina</guimenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1862
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choosing this context menu option opens a dialog in which you may define a "
"new group, or mailing list. See &nbsp;<link linkend=\"file-new-group\">the "
"appendix</link> for a detailed explanation."
msgstr ""
"Z izbiro te možnosti kontekstnega menija se odpre pogovorno okno, v katerem "
"lahko določite novo skupino ali poštni seznam. Za podrobno razlago glejte "
"&nbsp;<link linkend=\"file-new-group\">priponko</link>."

#. Tag: guimenu
#: index.docbook:1868
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edit Contact ..."
msgstr "Uredi stik..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1869
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choosing this context menu option has exactly the same effect as clicking "
"the <guibutton><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-edit.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>Edit "
"Contact...</guibutton> button on the Toolbar. See <link linkend=\"how-to-add-"
"a-new-contact\">chapter 2 above</link> for complete details."
msgstr ""
"Izbira te možnosti kontekstnega menija ima popolnoma enak učinek kot klik na "
"gumb <guibutton><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-edit.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></"
"inlinemediaobject>Uredi stik...</guibutton> v orodni vrstici. Za vse "
"podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"how-to-add-a-new-contact\">poglavje 2 "
"zgoraj</link>."

#. Tag: guimenu
#: index.docbook:1875
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export&nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;"
msgstr "Izvozi &nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This context menu function allows you to export selected contact data in "
"either <acronym>vCard</acronym> or <acronym>csv</acronym> format."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija kontekstnega menija omogoča izvoz izbranih podatkov o stikih v "
"obliki <acronym>vCard</acronym> ali <acronym>csv</acronym>."

#. Tag: guimenu
#: index.docbook:1881
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy Contact To &nbsp; &gt;"
msgstr "Kopiraj Kontakt v &nbsp; &gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1883
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This context menu choice lets you copy the selected contact(s) to a variable "
"destination. The list of destinations displayed when this option is chosen "
"depends on how many address books you have created."
msgstr ""
"Ta izbira v kontekstnem meniju omogoča kopiranje izbranega(-ih) stika(-ov) v "
"spremenljiv cilj. Seznam namembnih krajev, ki se prikaže, ko izberete to "
"možnost, je odvisen od tega, koliko imenikov ste ustvarili."

#. Tag: guimenu
#: index.docbook:1888
#, no-c-format
msgid "Move Contact To &nbsp; &gt;"
msgstr "Premakni stik v &nbsp; &gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1890
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Works just like the <quote>Copy Contact To</quote> operation described "
"above, except that it deletes the source data, instead of creating an extra "
"copy of it."
msgstr ""
"Deluje enako kot zgoraj opisana operacija <quote>Kopiraj stik v</quote>, le "
"da izbriše izvorne podatke in ne ustvari njihove dodatne kopije."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>P</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-print.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></"
"inlinemediaobject>Print</guimenu>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>P</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-print.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></"
"inlinemediaobject>Tiskanje</guimenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1897
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choosing this context menu item opens a printer selection dialog. Use the "
"<menuchoice><guisubmenu><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-preview-archive.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></"
"inlinemediaobject>Print Preview</guisubmenu> </menuchoice> dialog below to "
"set up the range of names and the print format before you select this "
"function."
msgstr ""
"Z izbiro tega elementa kontekstnega menija se odpre pogovorno okno za izbiro "
"tiskanja. Uporabite spodnje pogovorno okno "
"<menuchoice><guisubmenu><inlinemediaobject> <imageobject><imagedata fileref="
"\"document-preview-archive.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></"
"inlinemediaobject>Predogled tiskanja</guisubmenu> </menuchoice>, da "
"nastavite obseg imen in obliko tiskanja, preden izberete to funkcijo."

#. Tag: guimenu
#: index.docbook:1904
#, no-c-format
msgid "Print Preview"
msgstr "Predogled tiska"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1905
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This context menu option opens a print preview dialog, which also permits "
"you to format the report, select which items to include, and specify a sort "
"order, &etc; See &nbsp;<link linkend=\"file-print-preview\">the appendix</"
"link> for further details."
msgstr ""
"Ta možnost kontekstnega menija odpre pogovorno okno za predogled tiskanja, "
"ki omogoča tudi oblikovanje poročila, izbiro elementov, ki jih želite "
"vključiti, in določitev vrstnega reda &etc; Za več podrobnosti glejte &nbsp;"
"<link linkend=\"file-print-preview\">prilogo</link>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"press\">&Del;</keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"edit-"
"delete.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>Delete "
"Contact</guimenu>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"press\">&Del;</keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"edit-"
"delete.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>Izbriši stik</"
"guimenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1912
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete the selected contact(s) from the current address book."
msgstr "Izbriši izbrane stike iz trenutnega imenika."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1922
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Individual Contact Context Menu"
msgstr "Kontekstni meni posameznega stika"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1926
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>A screenshot of &kaddressbook;'s <quote>Individual Contact</"
"quote> context menu.</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo>Posnetek zaslona <quote>Individualni stik</quote> kontekstnega "
"menija v &kaddressbook;.</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:1932
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>A screenshot of &kaddressbook;'s <quote>Individual Contact</quote> "
"context menu.</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>Posnetek zaslona <quote>Individualni stik</quote> kontekstnega "
"menija v &kaddressbook;.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1935
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kaddressbook;'s <quote>Individual Contact</quote> context menu."
msgstr "Kontekstni meni <quote>Individualni stik</quote> v &kaddressbook;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on which data item you select, the caption in this context menu "
"may vary. But in every case, the function is the same: the selected data "
"item is copied to the clipboard."
msgstr ""
"Napis v tem kontekstnem meniju se lahko razlikuje glede na to, kateri "
"podatkovni element izberete. V vsakem primeru pa je funkcija enaka: izbrani "
"podatkovni element se kopira v odložišče."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:1957
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>AIM</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>AIM</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1958
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>AIM</acronym> stands for America Online Instant Messaging. AIM was "
"an early leader in the competitive IM marketplace, but fell into disfavor as "
"AOL itself became less popular. The original service was discontinued in "
"2017, but fans have kept it running <ulink url=\"http://iwarg.ddns.net/aim/"
"\">at this web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>AIM</acronym> pomeni America Online Instant Messaging. AIM je bil "
"na začetku vodilni na konkurenčnem trgu IM, vendar je padel v nemilost, ko "
"je sam AOL postal manj priljubljen. Prvotna storitev je bila ukinjena leta "
"2017, vendar so jo oboževalci ohranili <ulink url=\"http://iwarg.ddns.net/"
"aim/\">na tej spletni strani</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1965
#, no-c-format
msgid "&akonadi;"
msgstr "&akonadi;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1966
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An extensible cross-desktop storage service for &PIM; data and meta data "
"providing concurrent read, write, and query access. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"
"&akonadi; can be manipulated with the akonadictl command: enter "
"<quote>akonadictl --help</quote> in a console window to learn more."
msgstr ""
"Razširljiva medpredstavnostna storitev shranjevanja podatkov &PIM; in meta "
"podatkov, ki omogoča hkratno branje, pisanje in poizvedovanje. &nbsp;&nbsp;"
"&nbsp;&nbsp;&akonadi; lahko upravljate z ukazom akonadictl: za več "
"informacij v konzolno okno vnesite <quote>akonadictl --help</quote>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1972
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cloud-based service"
msgstr "Storitev v oblaku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any provider of data storage and data processing resources residing in some "
"<quote>cloud</quote> of servers one may access via the internet."
msgstr ""
"Vsak ponudnik virov za shranjevanje in obdelavo podatkov, ki se nahajajo v "
"nekem <quote>oblaku</quote> strežnikov, do katerih lahko dostopate prek "
"interneta."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1978
#, no-c-format
msgid ".csv"
msgstr ".csv"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1979
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Comma Separated Values (or <filename class=\"extension\">.csv</filename>) "
"file is a plain text document in which each line, or record, is divided into "
"fields by a specific separator character, usually a comma. The <filename "
"class=\"extension\">.csv</filename> format dates back to the early days of "
"computing. It is still widely used, mainly because it is conceptually so "
"simple."
msgstr ""
"Comma separated values (Datoteka z vrednostmi, ločenimi z vejico) (ali "
"<filename class=\"extension\">.csv</filename>), je navaden besedilni "
"dokument, v katerem je vsaka vrstica ali zapis razdeljen na polja z "
"določenim ločilnim znakom, običajno vejico. Format <filename class="
"\"extension\">.csv</filename> izvira iz zgodnjih dni računalništva. Še vedno "
"se pogosto uporablja, predvsem zato, ker je konceptualno tako preprost."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:1986
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>DAV</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>DAV</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1987
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>DAV</acronym> stands for Distributed Authoring and Versioning, "
"which exists in several <quote>flavors</quote>, such as WebDAV (for creating "
"pages on the internet), GroupDAV (for groupware, open source software "
"authored by a group of collaborators), and CalDAV (calendar management for "
"groups), each one of which helps connect open source clients with open "
"source servers."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>DAV</acronym> je kratica za Distributed Authoring and Versioning, "
"ki obstaja v več <quote>oblikah</quote>, kot so WebDAV (za ustvarjanje "
"strani v internetu), GroupDAV (za skupinsko programsko opremo, odprtokodno "
"programsko opremo, katere avtorji so skupina sodelavcev) in CalDAV "
"(upravljanje koledarja za skupine), pri čemer vsaka od njih pomaga povezati "
"odprtokodne odjemalce z odprtokodnimi strežniki."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:1994
#, no-c-format
msgid "DIGEST-MD5"
msgstr "DIGEST-MD5"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>DIGEST-MD5</acronym> is an authentication technique used to set up "
"secure communications between a client and an internet service. It gets its "
"name from the MD5 hashing function used to encode the client's credentials. "
"See <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digest_access_authentication"
"\">this Wikipedia article</ulink> to learn more about it."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>DIGEST-MD5</acronym> je tehnika avtentikacije, ki se uporablja za "
"vzpostavitev varne komunikacije med odjemalcem in internetno storitvijo. Ime "
"je dobila po funkciji MD5, ki se uporablja za kodiranje poverilnic "
"odjemalca. Za več informacij o njem glejte <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Digest_access_authentication\">članek na Wikipediji</ulink>."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2002
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>EWS</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>EWS</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2003
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>EWS</acronym> stands for Exchange Web Services, &nbsp;&Microsoft;'s "
"set of proprietary protocols for exchanging personal data between internet "
"servers and end users, or clients. &nbsp;&nbsp;<glossterm linkend=\"gloss-"
"kolab\">Kolab</glossterm> provides similar functionality."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>EWS</acronym> pomeni Exchange Web Services, &nbsp;&nbsp;Microsoftov "
"nabor lastniških protokolov za izmenjavo osebnih podatkov med internetnimi "
"strežniki in končnimi uporabniki ali odjemalci. &nbsp;&nbsp;<glossterm "
"linkend=\"gloss-kolab\">Kolab</glossterm> zagotavlja podobne funkcije."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2009
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gadu-Gadu"
msgstr "Gadu-Gadu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2010
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gadu-Gadu (aka GG) is the most popular instant-messaging app in Poland."
msgstr ""
"Gadu-Gadu (tudi GG) je najbolj priljubljena aplikacija za takojšnje "
"sporočanje na Poljskem."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2014
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>GMX</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>GMX</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>GMX</acronym> stands for Global Mail eXchange (or, in Germany, "
"Global Message eXchange), a free advertising-supported email service. Visit "
"either <ulink url=\"https://www.gmx.net/\">this web site</ulink> or <ulink "
"url=\"https://www.gmx.com/\">this one</ulink> to learn more about it."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>GMX</acronym> je kratica za Global Mail eXchange (ali v Nemčiji "
"Global Message eXchange), brezplačno e-poštno storitev, podprto z "
"oglaševanjem. Za več informacij o njem obiščite <ulink url=\"https://www.gmx."
"net/\">to spletno mesto</ulink> ali <ulink url=\"https://www.gmx.com/"
"\">tega</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2021
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gravatar"
msgstr "Gravatar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Gravatar, or Globally Recognized Avatar, is a graphic image associated "
"with a WordPress user's email address. It is usually displayed as an 80px X "
"80px graphic image. Since many bloggers use WordPress software, the Gravatar "
"is widely available."
msgstr ""
"Gravatar ali globalno prepoznavni avatar je grafična podoba, povezana z e-"
"poštnim naslovom uporabnika WordPressa. Običajno se prikaže kot grafična "
"slika velikosti 80px X 80px. Ker veliko blogerjev uporablja programsko "
"opremo WordPress, je Gravatar široko dostopen."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2028
#, no-c-format
msgid "GroupWise"
msgstr "GroupWise"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2029
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GroupWise Messenger is an instant messaging service sponsored by Micro Focus "
"International plc, a software company located in Newbury, Berkshire, "
"England. You can get a copy of the Messenger software from <ulink url="
"\"https://mail.dcbe.org:8300/\">this web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"GroupWise Messenger je storitev takojšnjega sporočanja, ki jo sponzorira "
"podjetje Micro Focus International plc, podjetje za programsko opremo s "
"sedežem v Newburyju, Berkshire, Anglija. Kopijo programske opreme Messenger "
"lahko dobite na <ulink url=\"https://mail.dcbe.org:8300/\">tem spletnem "
"mestu</ulink>."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2035
#, no-c-format
msgid "GSSAPI"
msgstr "GSSAPI"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2036
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>GSSAPI</acronym> stands for Generic Security Service Application "
"Program Interface, a sort of <quote>dictionary</quote> for the many security "
"protocols in use on the internet. It consists of a program library and a set "
"of standard subroutine calls that allow an internet client to determine "
"which particular security protocol an internet service is using, and then to "
"encode/decode the user's credentials appropriately."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>GSSAPI</acronym> je kratica za Generic Security Service Application "
"Program Interface, nekakšen <quote>slovar</quote> za številne varnostne "
"protokole, ki se uporabljajo v internetu. Sestavljen je iz programske "
"knjižnice in niza standardnih klicev podprogramov, ki internetnemu odjemalcu "
"omogočajo, da določi, kateri varnostni protokol uporablja internetna "
"storitev, in nato ustrezno kodira/dekodira uporabnikove poverilnice."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2043
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>ICQ</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>ICQ</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2044
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>ICQ</acronym> is not precisely an acronym: it's a pun meant to "
"sound like <quote>I Seek You</quote>. It is one of the original IM "
"platforms, first coming online in 1996. The software is available for "
"download <ulink url=\"https://icq.com/linux/en\">here</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>ICQ</acronym> ni ravno kratica: gre za besedno igro, ki naj bi "
"zvenela kot <quote>I Seek You</quote>. Gre za eno od izvirnih platform za "
"IM, ki je bila prvič na voljo leta 1996. Programska oprema je na voljo za "
"prenos <ulink url=\"https://icq.com/linux/en\">tu</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2050
#, no-c-format
msgid "&IMAP;"
msgstr "&IMAP;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2051
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&IMAP; stands for Internet Message Access Protocol, a widely available "
"method for managing email messages. &IMAP; maintains and synchronizes local "
"and remote copies of a set of messages -- in other words, the locally stored "
"data for an &IMAP; account are a mirror image of the messages on the server."
msgstr ""
"&IMAP; pomeni protokol za dostop do internetnih sporočil, ki je splošno "
"dostopna metoda za upravljanje e-poštnih sporočil. &IMAP; vzdržuje in "
"sinhronizira lokalne in oddaljene kopije niza sporočil - z drugimi besedami, "
"lokalno shranjeni podatki za račun &IMAP; so zrcalna slika sporočil v "
"strežniku."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2058
#, no-c-format
msgid "Inline OpenPGP"
msgstr "Inline OpenPGP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2059
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Inline OpenPGP is an encryption protocol in which PGP signatures are "
"directly embedded in the body of the email message. This protocol is "
"deprecated because of technical difficulties caused by the indiscriminate "
"use of non-ASCII characters in plain-text email messages."
msgstr ""
"Inline OpenPGP je protokol šifriranja, pri katerem so podpisi PGP neposredno "
"vgrajeni v telo e-poštnega sporočila. Ta protokol je zastarel zaradi "
"tehničnih težav, ki jih povzroča neselektivna uporaba znakov, ki niso znaki "
"ASCII, v e-poštnih sporočilih v navadnem besedilu."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2066
#, no-c-format
msgid "&irc;"
msgstr "&irc;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2067
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&irc; stands for Internet Relay Chat, an IM service that has its roots in a "
"Finnish predecessor of the World Wide Web called OuluBox (1988). &irc; has "
"been losing users steadily for many years as social media platforms like "
"Facebook have become more popular. One larger remaining network is Libera "
"Chat; it can be accessed <ulink url=\"https://web.libera.chat/\">via this "
"web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"&irc; je kratica za Internet Relay Chat, storitev IM, ki izvira iz finskega "
"predhodnika svetovnega spleta OuluBox (1988). &irc; že več let vztrajno "
"izgublja uporabnike, saj so postale bolj priljubljene platforme družbenih "
"medijev, kot je Facebook. Večje preostalo omrežje je Libera Chat; do njega "
"lahko dostopate <ulink url=\"https://web.libera.chat/\">s tem spletnim "
"mestom</ulink>."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2075
#, no-c-format
msgid "ISDN"
msgstr "ISDN"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2076
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>ISDN</acronym> stands for Integrated Services Data Network, the "
"very first set of telecommunication standards that permitted the "
"simultaneous transmission of analog voice signals and digital data signals "
"over a switched network of copper wires (&ie; the old-style telephone "
"system). <acronym>ISDN</acronym> was unavoidable in the early days of the "
"Internet, but has lately been supplanted by more robust technologies that "
"permit unswitched connections over networks that utilize fiber optic cables, "
"satellites, and very high frequency microwave transmitters / receivers. It "
"is still widely used in a few industrial applications where a direct point-"
"to-point connection is necessary, but is on the way out in the broader "
"consumer market."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>ISDN</acronym> je kratica za Integrated Services Data Network, prvi "
"sklop telekomunikacijskih standardov, ki je omogočal hkratni prenos "
"analognih govornih signalov in digitalnih podatkovnih signalov prek "
"komutiranega omrežja bakrenih žic (stari telefonski sistem). <acronym>ISDN</"
"acronym> je bil neizogiben v zgodnjih dneh interneta, vendar so ga v zadnjem "
"času nadomestile zanesljivejše tehnologije, ki omogočajo nekomutirane "
"povezave prek omrežij z optičnimi kabli, sateliti in mikrovalovnimi "
"oddajniki/ sprejemniki zelo visoke frekvence. Še vedno se pogosto uporablja "
"v nekaterih industrijskih aplikacijah, kjer je potrebna neposredna povezava "
"točka-točka, na širšem potrošniškem trgu pa je v zatonu."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2086
#, no-c-format
msgid "Jabber"
msgstr "Jabber"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2087
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Jabber is an instant-messaging service that relies on the <glossterm linkend="
"\"gloss-xmpp\"><acronym>XMPP</acronym> </glossterm> protocol. The original "
"<quote>Jabber</quote> web site is no longer accepting new registrations, but "
"the <acronym>XMPP</acronym> protocol is in widespread use. See <ulink url="
"\"https://xmpp.org/about/\">this web site</ulink> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Jabber je storitev takojšnjega sporočanja, ki temelji na protokolu "
"<glossterm linkend=\"gloss-xmpp\"><acronym>XMPP</acronym> </glossterm>. "
"Prvotno spletno mesto <quote>Jabber</quote> ne sprejema več novih "
"registracij, vendar je protokol <acronym>XMPP</acronym> zelo razširjen. Za "
"več informacij glejte <ulink url=\"https://xmpp.org/about/\">to spletno "
"mesto</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2094
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kmail;"
msgstr "&kmail;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2095
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kde;'s email management program. Provides a fully integrated environment "
"for sending and receiving email messages from one (or more) email "
"account(s), maintaining as many email identities as you want to have, "
"organizing and archiving your old email messages, and managing your personal "
"email encryption keys."
msgstr ""
"&kde;jev program za upravljanje e-pošte. Zagotavlja popolnoma integrirano "
"okolje za pošiljanje in prejemanje e-poštnih sporočil iz enega (ali več) e-"
"poštnih računov, vzdrževanje poljubnega števila e-poštnih identitet, "
"urejanje in arhiviranje starih e-poštnih sporočil ter upravljanje osebnih "
"ključev za šifriranje e-pošte."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kolab"
msgstr "Kolab"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Kolab Systems AG is a corporation headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland that "
"provides both proprietary and open source software tools to facilitate "
"collaboration among groups of people who share data, messages, and "
"calendaring / scheduling resources via the internet. &nbsp;<glossterm "
"linkend=\"gloss-ews\">EWS</glossterm> &nbsp;provides similar, though wholly "
"proprietary, software packages."
msgstr ""
"Kolab Systems AG je korporacija s sedežem v Zürichu v Švici, ki zagotavlja "
"lastniška in odprtokodna programska orodja za lažje sodelovanje med "
"skupinami ljudi, ki si prek interneta izmenjujejo podatke, sporočila in "
"koledarje/razporede. &nbsp;<glossterm linkend=\"gloss-ews\">EWS</glossterm> "
"&nbsp;zagotavlja podobne, čeprav popolnoma lastniške programske pakete."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2111
#, no-c-format
msgid "LDAP"
msgstr "LDAP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (or &nbsp;<acronym>ldap</acronym>) "
"is a standard protocol, or method, for sharing some particular classes of "
"information among the many server computers that comprise the internet."
msgstr ""
"Protokol lahkega dostopa do imenikov (ali &nbsp;<acronym>ldap</acronym>) je "
"standardni protokol ali metoda za izmenjavo nekaterih posebnih razredov "
"informacij med številnimi strežniki, ki sestavljajo internet."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2118
#, no-c-format
msgid ".ldif"
msgstr ".ldif"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <glossterm linkend=\"gloss-ldap\"><acronym>LDAP</acronym></glossterm> "
"Data Interchange Format (or <filename class=\"extension\">.ldif</filename>) "
"file is a type of plain text file designed for exchanging directory "
"information among the various servers in a distributed network."
msgstr ""
"Datoteka <glossterm linkend=\"gloss-ldap\"><acronym>LDAP</acronym></"
"glossterm>Format za izmenjavo podatkov (ali <filename class=\"extension\">."
"ldif</filename>) je vrsta navadne besedilne datoteke, ki je namenjena "
"izmenjavi informacij o imeniku med različnimi strežniki v distribuiranem "
"omrežju."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Meanwhile"
msgstr "Meanwhile"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Meanwhile</quote> is open source software designed to communicate "
"with IBM's <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM_Sametime"
"\"><quote>Sametime</quote></ulink> instant messaging software. See <ulink "
"url=\"https://github.com/obriencj/meanwhile\">this web site</ulink> if you "
"want to learn more about it."
msgstr ""
"<quote>Meanwhile</quote> je odprtokodna programska oprema, zasnovana za "
"komunikacijo z IBM-ovo <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"IBM_Sametime\"><quote>Sametime</quote></ulink> programsko opremo za "
"takojšnje sporočanje. Če želite o tem izvedeti več, glejte <ulink url="
"\"https://github.com/obriencj/meanwhile\">to spletno mesto</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2134
#, no-c-format
msgid "&MIME;"
msgstr "&MIME;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&MIME; stands for Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions, a set of coding "
"conventions designed to make email messages more flexible by enabling "
"features like extended character sets, embedded images, <quote>rich text</"
"quote> coding, &etc; The original email coding conventions supported nothing "
"besides plain text (or encrypted) messages written with 7-bit ASCII code. "
"Almost all contemporary email messages are &MIME; encoded."
msgstr ""
"&MIME; pomeni Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (večnamenske razširitve "
"internetne pošte), niz kodirnih konvencij, ki so namenjene večji "
"prilagodljivosti e-poštnih sporočil, saj omogočajo funkcije, kot so "
"razširjeni nabori znakov, vstavljene slike, kodiranje <quote>bogatega "
"besedila</quote> itd.; Prvotne konvencije za kodiranje e-pošte so poleg "
"navadnih besedilnih (ali šifriranih) sporočil, napisanih s 7-bitno kodo "
"ASCII, podpirale samo še sporočila. Skoraj vsa sodobna e-poštna sporočila so "
"kodirana v &MIME;."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2143
#, no-c-format
msgid "OpenPGP/&MIME;"
msgstr "OpenPGP/&MIME;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"OpenPGP/&MIME; refers to an encryption convention for <glossterm linkend="
"\"gloss-acro-mime\">&MIME;</glossterm> encoded email messages. A special set "
"of &MIME; headers are wrapped around the PGP signature, allowing an email "
"client program to conceal the signature when the message is displayed."
msgstr ""
"OpenPGP/&MIME; se nanaša na konvencijo šifriranja za <glossterm linkend="
"\"gloss-acro-mime\">&MIME;</glossterm> kodirana e-poštna sporočila. Podpis "
"PGP je ovit s posebnim nizom glave &MIME;, kar odjemalcu e-pošte omogoča, da "
"ob prikazu sporočila skrije podpis."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open-Xchange Groupware Server"
msgstr "Open-Xchange Groupware Server"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open-Xchange AG is a corporation headquartered in Cologne, Germany that "
"provides both proprietary and open source software tools to facilitate "
"collaboration among groups of people who share data, messages, and "
"calendaring / scheduling resources via the internet. &nbsp;<glossterm "
"linkend=\"gloss-ews\">EWS</glossterm> &nbsp;and &nbsp;<glossterm linkend="
"\"gloss-kolab\">Kolab</glossterm> provide similar software packages."
msgstr ""
"Open-Xchange AG je korporacija s sedežem v Kölnu v Nemčiji, ki zagotavlja "
"lastniška in odprtokodna programska orodja za lažje sodelovanje med "
"skupinami ljudi, ki si prek interneta izmenjujejo podatke, sporočila in "
"koledarje/razporede. &nbsp;<glossterm linkend=\"gloss-ews\">EWS</glossterm> "
"&nbsp;in &nbsp;<glossterm linkend=\"gloss-kolab\">Kolab</glossterm> "
"zagotavljata podobne programske pakete."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2160
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>PCS</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>PCS</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>PCS</acronym> stands for Personal Communication Service, which is "
"basically a cell phone with some extra functionality built in. <acronym>PCS</"
"acronym> phones operate on a higher frequency band than traditional cell "
"phones, which implies that they can provide more bandwidth than older cell "
"phones."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>PCS</acronym> je kratica za Personal Communication Service, ki je v "
"bistvu mobilni telefon z vgrajenimi dodatnimi funkcijami. <acronym>PCS</"
"acronym> telefoni delujejo v višjem frekvenčnem pasu kot običajni mobilni "
"telefoni, kar pomeni, da lahko zagotavljajo večjo pasovno širino kot "
"starejši mobilni telefoni."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2168
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>PGP</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>PGP</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>PGP</acronym> stands for Pretty Good Privacy, a data-encryption "
"program that was released by Philip Zimmerman in 1991. Most email encryption "
"software in use today employs some variant of PGP to encrypt, decrypt, and "
"cryptographically sign messages."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>PGP</acronym> je kratica za program za šifriranje podatkov Pretty "
"Good Privacy, ki ga je leta 1991 izdal Philip Zimmerman. Večina programske "
"opreme za šifriranje e-pošte, ki se danes uporablja, uporablja neko "
"različico programa PGP za šifriranje, dešifriranje in kriptografsko "
"podpisovanje sporočil."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2175
#, no-c-format
msgid "&PIM;"
msgstr "&PIM;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kde;'s Personal Information Management system, a suite of programs to help "
"you manage your contacts and your schedule. &PIM; includes &kontact;, &nbsp;"
"&kmail;, &nbsp;&kaddressbook;, &nbsp;&korganizer;, &nbsp;&akregator;, and "
"&nbsp;&akonadi;. Also used more generally to describe any system for "
"managing personal information such as names, addresses, telephone numbers, "
"&etc;"
msgstr ""
"&kde; je sistem za upravljanje osebnih podatkov, sklop programov za "
"upravljanje stikov in urnika. &PIM; vključuje &kontact;, &nbsp;&kmail;, "
"&nbsp;&kaddressbook;, &nbsp;&korganizer;, &nbsp;&akregator; in &nbsp;"
"&akonadi;. Uporablja se tudi na splošno za opis katerega koli sistema za "
"upravljanje osebnih podatkov, kot so imena, naslovi, telefonske številke "
"&etc;"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2184
#, no-c-format
msgid "QR Code"
msgstr "QR Code"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QR Code stands for Quick Response Code, a two-dimensional barcode used to "
"represent digital data. It was invented in Japan in 1994 for use by "
"automobile manufacturers, but has spread far and wide, so that it is "
"ubiquitous today."
msgstr ""
"Koda QR je kratica za kodo hitrega odziva, dvodimenzionalno črtno kodo, ki "
"se uporablja za predstavitev digitalnih podatkov. Izumili so ga na Japonskem "
"leta 1994 za uporabo pri proizvajalcih avtomobilov, vendar se je razširil "
"daleč naokoli, tako da je danes vseprisoten."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2191
#, no-c-format
msgid "SASL"
msgstr "SASL"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>SASL</acronym> stands for Simple Authentication and Security Layer, "
"a framework for client authentication (passwords and usernames) and data "
"security (encrypted connections). It supports more than a dozen different "
"protocols."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>SASL</acronym> je kratica za Simple Authentication and Security "
"Layer, ogrodje za preverjanje pristnosti odjemalcev (gesla in uporabniška "
"imena) in varnost podatkov (šifrirane povezave). Podpira več kot deset "
"različnih protokolov."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2198
#, no-c-format
msgid "S/MIME"
msgstr "S/MIME"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> stands for Secure / Multipurpose Internet Mail "
"Extensions, a standard cryptographic method for signing, encrypting, abd "
"decrypting email messages. Unlike <glossterm linkend=\"gloss-pgp"
"\"><acronym>PGP</acronym></glossterm>, which uses private keys, <acronym>S/"
"MIME</acronym> uses publicly published encryption keys certified by a "
"Certificate Authority, such as <ulink url=\"https://www.verisign.com/"
"\">Verisign</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> je kratica za Secure / Multipurpose Internet Mail "
"Extensions, standardno kriptografsko metodo za podpisovanje, šifriranje in "
"dešifriranje e-poštnih sporočil. Za razliko od <glossterm linkend=\"gloss-pgp"
"\"><acronym>PGP</acronym></glossterm>, ki uporablja zasebne ključe, "
"<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> uporablja javno objavljene šifrirne ključe, ki jih "
"potrdi organ za potrjevanje, kot je <ulink url=\"https://www.verisign.com/"
"\">Verisign</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2207
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> Opaque"
msgstr "<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> Opaque"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> Opaque stands for the <quote>opaque</quote> "
"version of Secure / Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions. It is similar to "
"the <quote>S/MIME</quote> format defined above, but the entire contents of "
"the message are rolled up into a single &MIME; object. (Most &MIME; encoded "
"email messages consist of two or more separate &MIME; objects.)"
msgstr ""
"<acronym>S/MIME</acronym> Opaque pomeni <quote>opaque</quote> različico "
"Secure / Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions. Podoben je zgoraj "
"opredeljenemu formatu <quote>S/MIME</quote>, vendar je celotna vsebina "
"sporočila združena v en sam objekt &MIME;. (Večina kodiranih e-poštnih "
"sporočil &MIME; je sestavljena iz dveh ali več ločenih objektov &MIME;.)"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2215
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>SMS</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>SMS</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>SMS</acronym> stands for Short Message Service, a text-messaging "
"service built into most telephone, internet, and mobile device communication "
"networks. It facilitates the exchange of text messages that are less than "
"161 bytes long."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>SMS</acronym> je kratica za Short Message Service (storitev kratkih "
"sporočil), storitev za pošiljanje besedilnih sporočil, ki je vgrajena v "
"večino telefonskih in internetnih komunikacijskih omrežij ter omrežij "
"mobilnih naprav. Omogoča izmenjavo besedilnih sporočil, dolgih manj kot 161 "
"bajtov."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2222
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>SSL</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>SSL</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>SSL</acronym> stands for Secure Socket Layer, a deprecated "
"cryptographic protocol that has been largely supplanted by <acronym>TLS</"
"acronym>."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>SSL</acronym> je kratica za Secure Socket Layer, zastareli "
"kriptografski protokol, ki ga je večinoma nadomestil <acronym>TLS</acronym>."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>TLS</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>TLS</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>TLS</acronym> stands for Transport Layer Security, a cryptographic "
"protocol that is widely used to secure internet communications. Its primary "
"function is to allow a client and a server to exchange enough information "
"securely that they can set up a pair of encryption / decryption keys for use "
"during the rest of the internet session. <acronym>TLS</acronym> is the "
"weakest link in the chain connecting a client program to a secure "
"(encrypted) internet service. It has been the target of several hacking "
"exploits, and it has been revised several times in response to those attacks."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>TLS</acronym> je kratica za Transport Layer Security, kriptografski "
"protokol, ki se pogosto uporablja za zaščito internetnih komunikacij. "
"Njegova glavna funkcija je omogočiti odjemalcu in strežniku, da varno "
"izmenjata dovolj informacij, da lahko določita par šifrirnih/dešifrirnih "
"ključev za uporabo med preostalo internetno sejo. <acronym>TLS</acronym> je "
"najšibkejši člen v verigi, ki povezuje odjemalski program z varno "
"(šifrirano) internetno storitvijo. Bil je tarča več hekerskih napadov in je "
"bil zaradi teh napadov večkrat spremenjen."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:2238
#, no-c-format
msgid ".vcf"
msgstr ".vcf"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Virtual (business) Card Format (or <filename class=\"extension\">.vcf</"
"filename>) is a keyword-oriented data interchange format that has gone "
"through several iterations (2.0, 2.1, 3.0, &nbsp;&etc;) since its "
"introduction &nbsp;<emphasis>ca.</emphasis> 1990. The most recent version is "
"vCard 4.0."
msgstr ""
"Virtual (business) Card Format (Format virtualne (poslovne) kartice)(ali "
"<filename class=\"extension\">.vcf</filename>) je v ključne besede usmerjen "
"format za izmenjavo podatkov, ki je od svoje uvedbe &nbsp;<emphasis>ca.</"
"emphasis> leta 1990 doživel več iteracij (2.0, 2.1, 3.0, &nbsp;itd.). "
"Najnovejša različica je vCard 4.0."

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:2246
#, no-c-format
msgid "XMPP"
msgstr "XMPP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>XMPP</acronym> stands for Extensible Messaging and Presence "
"Protocol, the basic technological underpinning for the <quote>Jabber</quote> "
"instant messaging service."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>XMPP</acronym> je kratica za Extensible Messaging and Presence "
"Protocol, osnovno tehnološko podlago za storitev takojšnjega sporočanja "
"<quote>Jabber</quote>."
